<dl id="s17019cj"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="us17" href="#s17019cj">Ithaca: </a><a href="../../ff/unbs/s17all.htm#s17019cj">sector 19(cj)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> clock loses time in summer</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">The longer a pendulum is the slower it vibrates. Hence, show why <mark>a clock loses time in summer</mark> and gains in winter. <small> Wentworth and Hill, <a name="TBOP" href="/udra/udex.htm#tbop"><cite title="source">A Text-Book of Physics</cite></a> (1904), 104</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
